"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT loan.account_id)\nFROM loan\nJOIN account ON loan.account_id = account.account_id\nWHERE loan.date BETWEEN '1995-01-01' AND '1997-12-31'\n  AND loan.amount >= 250000\n  AND account.frequency = 'POPLATEK MESICNE';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct accounts that had loans approved between January 1, 1995, and December 31, 1997, with an amount of at least 250,000 and opted for monthly statement issuance. The `JOIN` operation connects the `loan` and `account` tables using the `account_id` foreign key relationship."